This paper is about the identification of cues that differentiate phishing emails from genuine emails, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications for education and training, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The study also involves data analysis and identification of relevant cues, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media (cs.SI).
